Governor Aminu Waziri Tambuwal of Sokoto state has directed the peoples living in areas affected by banditry to desist from using motorcycles as directed by President Muhammadu Buhari. “Don’t go to those areas used by bandits on motorcycles because if you are caught you will be treated like them,” he said He also urged the people of the state to be vigilant and rise against the enemies of the state. Briefing newsmen shortly after holding an emergency security meeting at the government house, the Governor described the recent attack and killing of the district head of Balle as barbaric, saying his government would do everything humanly possible to reverse the situation. He also called on the people of Burkusuma in Sabon Birni local government area who had fled to the neighbouring Niger Republic to return home that the government would guarantee their safety. The Governor further directed the security agencies to enforce security along Marnona-Isa road. He urged the people of the state to give reasonable information to security agencies on any suspicious movement in their areas. Suspected armed bandits kill 26 in Sokoto Bandits kill 26 in Sokoto Tambuwal appoints sole administrators for LGAs Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin